Heat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Lightly oil or butter a 12 hole muffin tray. Line the base and most of the sides of each mould with a slice of ham, then break an egg into the hollow.Drizzle with the cream, and scatter with sea salt, pepper, parsley and parmesan.Bake for 15-20 minutes until the egg is just set and starting to shrink away from the sides of the tin.Leave to cool for five minutes, then run a knife around each mould to loosen the ham and egg, and remove to a wire tray. Eat warm, or at room temperature.Serve with a handful of herb and baby leaf salad.